    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Susan Allen Toth certainly touched my heart in ''Home, When the Heart Is Elsewhere'' (July 23). She writes about the ''sly, mysterious and dazzling impulse'' to travel. The German language has a word for it -- fernweh, the exact opposite of heimweh, or homesickness -- and I am smitten with it. I am happy on returning from a trip only when I find a reason to plan the next one.</p>
        <p>HELGA KASIMOFF  Los Angeles</p>
      </block>
